reviews.text: Great service from pleasant staff,  could not find one fault with them.  My friend is in a wheelchair and the service was excellent.

Durham is just the most amazing city. Packed with history, beautiful architecture & more than enough things to do for all ages. I particularly recommend the indoor market for hidden gems & oddities and a row along the river. The riverside is paved with walkways all the way around with amazing views and the bars & bistros are everywhere.
Very helpful staff, very friendly people in general, nice station and easy to get about.  Parking a bit tricky when busy.  Taxis outside the station.
Great city, with the cathedral and castle overlooking the city. Plenty of places to eat and a few great shops and a wonderful indoor market.
This is a updated Station with Barcoded Technology for added security.
